CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F465A1778087158
OL,3,C'This is not a two-horse race' insists
OL,4,CDeputy First Minister after ITV poll
OL,6,FJames Evans, from Reform UK, argued, "
OL,7,FWhat we're hearing on the doorstep
OL,8,Fright across Wales isn't reflected in
OL,9,Fthat poll.
OL,11,F"A lot of people are coming over to
OL,12,FReform because they don't want the
OL,13,Fdivisive policies that are being
OL,14,Fpushed by Plaid Cymru and a potential
OL,15,Fcoalition partner in the Greens. But
OL,16,Fwe're fighting for every single vote
OL,17,Facross our country.
OL,19,F"We're a new party, a party that isn't
OL,20,Fpart of the cosy consensus that has
OL,21,Fbeen for 27 years in Cardiff Bay."
OL,26,@nD@fOUsD@AOU{D@AOU}D@bO]
